&lt;p&gt;Switchboard Operator – Part time (12.5 hours) Night Shift&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently seeking a professional individual with previous experience in switchboard duties. The individual must be professional, reliable, have excellent interpersonal skills and with excellent written English skills. In order to fulfil this role, candidates should have experience of operating a switchboard. You should also have excellent communication and computer skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Switchboard Operator role will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dealing with clients queries in a polite and professional manner, maintaining exceptional standards for customer service and upholding the Trust&#39;s professional image at all times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing telephone and email enquiries and maintaining accurate client records against the computer database.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Efficiently manage queries from customers in accordance with processes and guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist and support other team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Announce callers when transferring.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take accurate messages and forward accordingly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dealing emergency calls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be able to cover night shift duties based on a rota. You will work as part of a team but there will be shifts when you are a lone worker so must be able to do so. If you need any further information about the role or the shift patterns you are expected to cover please contact Julie Schofield on telephone number 01922 6566699 or email Julie.schofield@walsallhealthcare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
